What does Pivot mean in the startup landscape?
A company shifts its business strategy to accommodate changes in its industry, customer preferences, or any other factor that impacts its bottom line.

What is a Pitch deck?
A presentation deck that is used to pitch your idea or company to any number of audiences, generally investors.

When is a startup termed a Unicorn?
When it reaches the valuation of $1 billion.

What is an MVP?
A product with enough features to attract early-adopter customers and validate a product idea early in the product development cycle.

What is an Incubator?
A collaborative program designed to help new startups succeed.

What do we mean by Burn Rate?
The rate at which a new company is spending its venture capital to finance overhead before generating positive cash flow from operations.

When is a startup called Bootstrapped?
When a company started with little capital, relying on money other than outside investments.

What is an Angel Investment?
Investment where a high-net-worth individual funds startups at the early stages, often with their own money.

What's the difference between B2B and B2C?
B2C (business-to-consumer) is a process for selling products directly to consumers. 
B2B (business-to-business) is a process for selling products or services to other businesses.

What is an Exit Strategy?
A contingency plan that is executed by an investor, trader, venture capitalist, or business owner to liquidate a position in a financial 
asset or dispose of tangible business assets once predetermined criteria for either has been met or exceeded.

